note the deadline to request an absentee ballot is the SAME day. Must be received in county auditor's office by 8 pm that day. Postmark does not count.
How do you vote early?

Great to hear you want to vote early!

Iowa has two options:
1. In person: Visit your local polling place any time starting ***today***, October 16th! ([This site](https://sos.iowa.gov/elections/voterreg/pollingplace/search.aspx) can show your polling place.)
2. By mail: Request a mail ballot by 5 PM on October 21st. Then mail it so it arrives by 8 PM on November 5th, or drop it off in person at the county auditor.

There's also lots more information [right here](https://iwillvote.com/votinginfo/IA).
Do you know if my ID being expired is a bad thing cause it hasn‚Äôt been expired for too long

Good question! If you're already registered to vote, you can still use your driver's license if it's been expired for *90 days or less*.

If it's been expired longer, there are other options like a passport or a "voter ID", which you can get from the county.

[More info here](https://sos.iowa.gov/elections/voterinformation/voteridfaq.html) and in this PDF.

Do u know if ballet photos are illegal in Iowa?

Hmmm. I'm not 100% sure. [This article](https://www.vox.com/21523858/ballot-selfies-state-rules) from 2020 says it was okay, though. Folks at the courthouse might also be able to weigh in if you're still there.

[This page](https://www.ncsl.org/elections-and-campaigns/secrecy-of-the-ballot-and-ballot-selfies) says Iowa election officials have suggested two other good alternatives:
1. A selfie next to the "vote here sign"
2. A picture of the ballot box or kiosk itself, rather than the ballot
Ah okay
Ballot photos legality seems to vary from county to county, state to state.  It's tough for us to make a definitive call, here.  Best to check with your local people.
(We remove all ballot photos from this server just to help keep everyone on the safe side.)
